42
00:05:47,180 --> 00:05:48,530
Huh? What?

43
00:05:52,300 --> 00:05:54,770
My crown!
She's got my crown!

44
00:05:56,750 --> 00:05:58,200
Stop! Thief!

45
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:01,190
She's stolen my crown!

46
00:06:03,650 --> 00:06:04,800
Stop!

47
00:06:19,760 --> 00:06:21,900
What did you do with my crown?

48
00:06:22,030 --> 00:06:23,960
Sorry it had to be this way...

49
00:06:25,150 --> 00:06:26,520
Princess!

50
00:06:29,280 --> 00:06:31,790
Who was that?

51
00:06:33,530 --> 00:06:36,860
Sunset Shimmer.
A former student of mine.

52
00:06:36,990 --> 00:06:40,490
She began her studies with me
not long before Twilight.

53
00:06:40,620 --> 00:06:43,610
But when she did not get what
she wanted as quickly as she liked,

54
00:06:43,740 --> 00:06:45,790
she turned cruel and dishonest.

55
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:47,310
I tried to help her,

56
00:06:47,440 --> 00:06:51,460
but she eventually decided to abandon
her studies and pursue her own path.

57
00:06:51,590 --> 00:06:53,870
One that has sadly led her
to stealing your crown.

58
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:57,370
She replaced Twilight's
with this one.

59
00:06:57,500 --> 00:06:59,260
I suppose Sunset Shimmer thought

60
00:06:59,260 --> 00:07:01,840
you wouldn't notice right away
that this was not yours.

61
00:07:01,970 --> 00:07:03,075
And by the time you did,

62
00:07:03,076 --> 00:07:06,700
it would be too late to go after
your crown and Element of Harmony.

63
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:09,560
But I don't understand!
Where did she go?

64
00:07:09,690 --> 00:07:11,350
Why did she take the crown?

65
00:07:11,480 --> 00:07:14,730
You'll soon know more about
this place than even I do.

66
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:19,890
This is no ordinary mirror.

67
00:07:20,020 --> 00:07:22,330
It is a gateway to another world.

68
00:07:22,460 --> 00:07:26,130
A gateway that opens
once every thirty moons.

69
00:07:26,260 --> 00:07:28,380
Sparkly!

70
00:07:28,510 --> 00:07:31,590
It has always been kept in
the throne room of Canterlot Castle.

71
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:33,900
But when Princess Cadance
took over the Crystal Empire,

72
00:07:34,030 --> 00:07:36,010
we sent it here
for her to watch over.

73
00:07:36,140 --> 00:07:40,130
I had always hoped that Sunset Shimmer
would someday use it to return,

74
00:07:40,260 --> 00:07:43,520
to come back to Equestria
seeking my guidance.

75
00:07:43,650 --> 00:07:46,190
Obviously,
this is not what has happened.

76
00:07:46,450 --> 00:07:47,900
Twilight,

77
00:07:48,030 --> 00:07:50,750
you must use the mirror
to go into this other world

78
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:52,900
and retrieve your crown.

79
00:07:53,030 --> 00:07:55,580
Without it, the other Elements
of Harmony have no power

80
00:07:55,710 --> 00:07:59,750
and Equestria is left without one
of its most important means of defense.

81
00:08:02,700 --> 00:08:07,370
Your crown does not belong in the place
Sunset Shimmer now calls home.

82
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:09,999
And in her possession,
your Element of Harmony

83
00:08:10,129 --> 00:08:13,920
will no doubt be used to bring harm
to the inhabitants of this other realm.

84
00:08:14,280 --> 00:08:17,600
They will not have the power
to defend themselves.

85
00:08:18,930 --> 00:08:21,680
You understand
the importance of your task?

86
00:08:21,810 --> 00:08:23,360
Of course.

87
00:08:23,490 --> 00:08:25,560
Good. Then you must go at once.

88
00:08:31,620 --> 00:08:34,020
She's going,
we're going with her!

89
00:08:34,150 --> 00:08:35,500
Right, girls?

90
00:08:35,630 --> 00:08:38,180
Ooooh! I'm so 'nervicited'!

91
00:08:38,310 --> 00:08:41,320
You do realize that's not a real word,
right?

92
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:44,410
I'm afraid I can't let you go.

93
00:08:44,540 --> 00:08:46,580
What?! Why not?!

94
00:08:46,710 --> 00:08:50,450
Sending all of you could upset
the balance of this alternate world,

95
00:08:50,580 --> 00:08:52,467
creating havoc
that would make it impossible

96
00:08:52,597 --> 00:08:55,630
for Twilight to get the crown back
from Sunset Shimmer.

97
00:08:55,760 --> 00:08:58,840
This is something
Princess Twilight must do alone.

98
00:08:58,970 --> 00:09:00,480
Time is of the essence.

99
00:09:00,620 --> 00:09:04,260
On the third day, when the moon
reaches its peak in the night sky,

100
00:09:04,400 --> 00:09:07,130
the gateway will close.
And once it does,

101
00:09:07,260 --> 00:09:11,860
it will be another thirty moons before
you will be able to use it to return.

102
00:09:11,990 --> 00:09:15,610
- It's alright, Twi!
- You'll be back before you know it!

103
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:28,230
Spike, no!

104
00:09:37,330 --> 00:09:39,380
Huh, Twilight?

105
00:09:40,060 --> 00:09:42,830
Spike!
You're not supposed to...

106
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:46,180
Spike? Are you a...

107
00:09:46,180 --> 00:09:47,600
dog?

108
00:09:48,850 --> 00:09:51,120
I think so...

109
00:09:51,250 --> 00:09:54,800
But I have no idea what you are!

110
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:17,830
Twilight,
you have to get it together!

111
00:10:21,330 --> 00:10:24,180
What does the rest of me look like?

112
00:10:24,310 --> 00:10:27,280
Um, like you. Only not you.

113
00:10:27,410 --> 00:10:29,130
Your muzzle's really small.

114
00:10:29,260 --> 00:10:30,730
My muzzle?!

115
00:10:32,830 --> 00:10:34,580
Are you gonna scream again?

116
00:10:38,160 --> 00:10:40,630
Where are we?

117
00:10:42,070 --> 00:10:43,460
I don't know.

118
00:10:43,590 --> 00:10:46,530
But that must serve
as the gateway back to Equestria.

119
00:10:47,820 --> 00:10:50,730
We need to find my crown
as soon as possible and get back there.

120
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:55,750
I suggest we start searching
the castle first.

121
00:10:55,880 --> 00:10:57,100
Works for me.

122
00:11:05,920 --> 00:11:09,720
Yeah, I don't think that's how
the new you is supposed to–

123
00:11:21,560 --> 00:11:22,920
Come on, Spike.

124
00:11:23,050 --> 00:11:26,140
I do not wanna be like this
for longer than I have to.

125
00:11:26,270 --> 00:11:27,660
Look on the bright side.

126
00:11:27,790 --> 00:11:29,990
You don't have those pesky wings
to worry about anymore.

127
00:11:42,420 --> 00:11:44,760
My magic! It isn't working!

128
00:11:44,900 --> 00:11:45,960
Makes sense.

129
00:11:46,090 --> 00:11:47,880
You don't exactly have your horn.

130
00:11:48,010 --> 00:11:49,170
WHAT?!

131
00:11:49,300 --> 00:11:51,810
We really need to find you a mirror.

132
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:03,940
What do you think, Spike?

133
00:12:04,070 --> 00:12:06,610
Other artifacts she's stolen
from Equestria?

134
00:12:08,730 --> 00:12:10,830
What am I?

135
00:12:30,260 --> 00:12:31,850
You okay?

136
00:12:40,270 --> 00:12:43,000
I don't think this is a castle.

137
00:12:46,910 --> 00:12:51,060
<i>I've never seen a place
that's quite like this </i>

138
00:12:51,190 --> 00:12:53,060
<i>Everything is turned around</i>

139
00:12:53,190 --> 00:12:54,860
<i>This crazy world is upside-down </i>

140
00:12:54,990 --> 00:12:58,320
<i>Getting on my feet
it's the hand that I was dealt </i>

141
00:12:58,450 --> 00:13:00,399
<i>But I don't have
much time with them </i>

142
00:13:00,520 --> 00:13:02,530
<i>Got to learn all that I can </i>

143
00:13:09,920 --> 00:13:13,350
<i>They don't use any magic
or fly with any wings </i>

144
00:13:13,700 --> 00:13:17,600
<i>I don't get these funny clothes,
skinny legs or tiny nose </i>

145
00:13:17,730 --> 00:13:21,270
<i>Everything's confusing
when it seems so new </i>

146
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:25,320
<i>But I look a little closer
and it starts to feel familiar too </i>

147
00:13:31,420 --> 00:13:36,350
<i>What a strange new world
(what a strange new world) </i>

148
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:41,940
<i>I'm trying to make heads
or tails of this strange new world</i>

149
00:13:44,470 --> 00:13:50,030
<i>Sorting through the small details
of this strange new world </i>

150
00:13:50,500 --> 00:13:54,470
<i>What a strange new world </i>

151
00:14:02,700 --> 00:14:04,370
I'm really sorry.

152
00:14:04,500 --> 00:14:07,850
I just found it, and I thought
I should give it to her.

153
00:14:07,980 --> 00:14:10,410
I didn't know you had dropped it.

154
00:14:10,540 --> 00:14:11,620
Well, I did!

155
00:14:11,750 --> 00:14:14,990
And I was about to get it before
you swooped in and ruined everything!

156
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:17,770
You shouldn't pick up things
that don't belong to you.

157
00:14:17,900 --> 00:14:19,820
It... doesn't really
belong to you, either.

158
00:14:19,820 --> 00:14:22,050
Excuse me?!?

159
00:14:22,180 --> 00:14:23,910
Nothing...

160
00:14:24,030 --> 00:14:27,540
That's what I thought.
It's as good as mine, and you know it.

161
00:14:27,670 --> 00:14:28,900
You really are pathetic.

162
00:14:29,030 --> 00:14:32,360
It's no wonder your best friends
are all stray animals.

163
00:14:32,550 --> 00:14:34,770
How dare you speak to her that way!

164
00:14:36,170 --> 00:14:37,760
What did you say?

165
00:14:37,890 --> 00:14:39,260
I said...

166
00:14:39,390 --> 00:14:41,990
how dare you speak to her that way!

167
00:14:44,870 --> 00:14:46,980
You must be new here.

168
00:14:47,570 --> 00:14:50,770
I can speak to anyone any way I want.

169
00:14:54,430 --> 00:14:57,120
I can't believe you did that!

170
00:14:57,250 --> 00:14:58,940
I couldn't just stand there.

171
00:14:59,070 --> 00:15:02,950
Well, it's just that nobody ever
stands up to Sunset Shimmer.

172
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:04,790
Sunset Shimmer?

173
00:15:06,790 --> 00:15:09,250
- You've heard of her?
- Sort of...

174
00:15:09,380 --> 00:15:11,560
I don't think
I've seen you around before.

175
00:15:11,690 --> 00:15:14,930
Did you just transfer to Canterlot High
from another school?

176
00:15:15,970 --> 00:15:19,080
Yes! Another... school!

177
00:15:19,210 --> 00:15:21,010
My name's Twilight.

178
00:15:21,890 --> 00:15:24,150
I'm... Fluttershy.

179
00:15:24,280 --> 00:15:26,240
Sorry, what was that?

180
00:15:26,370 --> 00:15:28,050
It's Fluttershy!

181
00:15:28,180 --> 00:15:32,190
It sounds like you're saying Fluttershy,
but how can that...?

182
00:15:32,780 --> 00:15:37,170
Oh, my goodness!
Who's this sweet little guy?

183
00:15:37,300 --> 00:15:40,660
That's Spike! My, uh... dog!

184
00:15:40,790 --> 00:15:43,650
Oh, he's so cute!

185
00:15:43,850 --> 00:15:45,910
Go on, eat up, little pup!

186
00:15:50,170 --> 00:15:54,390
Wouldn't you just give anything
to know what they're really thinking?

187
00:15:54,520 --> 00:15:56,380
He usually just tells me.

188
00:15:56,510 --> 00:15:58,250
Oh, what do you mean?

189
00:16:00,470 --> 00:16:03,350
Oh, uh, nothing! Never mind.

190
00:16:03,700 --> 00:16:06,010
Sunset Shimmer said
you picked something up.

191
00:16:06,140 --> 00:16:07,840
Something that belonged to her.

192
00:16:07,970 --> 00:16:09,810
It wasn't a crown, was it?

193
00:16:09,940 --> 00:16:11,640
How did you know?

194
00:16:11,770 --> 00:16:13,080
Uh, lucky guess?

195
00:16:13,210 --> 00:16:14,480
Do you still have it?

196
00:16:15,880 --> 00:16:17,910
But you know what happened to it.

197
00:16:18,900 --> 00:16:22,230
This morning, I was passing out
flyers for the animal shelter

198
00:16:22,360 --> 00:16:24,240
<i>like I do every Wednesday.</i>

199
00:16:24,370 --> 00:16:27,120
Canterlot's animal shelter
needs more volunteers.

200
00:16:27,250 --> 00:16:30,400
Won't you help an animal
that can't help itself?

201
00:16:39,460 --> 00:16:41,800
<i>I have no idea how it got there. </i>

202
00:16:41,930 --> 00:16:43,534
But I didn't want anything
to happen to it,

203
00:16:43,665 --> 00:16:46,050
so I decided to give it
to Principal Celestia.

204
00:16:46,180 --> 00:16:50,220
Principal Celestia?
She's the ruler here?

205
00:16:50,350 --> 00:16:52,510
You could say that.

206
00:16:52,640 --> 00:16:56,770
Technically, I guess she and
Vice Principal Luna do make the rules.

207
00:16:56,900 --> 00:16:59,450
- Where is she now?
- Probably in her office.

208
00:17:02,030 --> 00:17:03,470
Third door on your left.

209
00:17:03,470 --> 00:17:04,680
Thank you!

210
00:17:05,050 --> 00:17:05,860
Oh, wait!

211
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:10,120
You're not really supposed
to have pets on school grounds.

212
00:17:10,250 --> 00:17:12,270
Might wanna tuck him
into your backpack.

213
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:13,850
That's what I do!

214
00:17:16,550 --> 00:17:19,970
They just get so lonely
when I'm in school all day.

215
00:17:20,100 --> 00:17:22,790
Oh, okay! Thank you!

216
00:17:22,980 --> 00:17:25,140
Oh, no! I'm late for class!

217
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:30,780
Come in.

218
00:17:34,060 --> 00:17:35,150
How may I help you?

219
00:17:45,860 --> 00:17:49,060
My name's Twilight Sparkle.
I'm new here, and...

220
00:17:49,190 --> 00:17:53,330
Well, I understand that Fluttershy found
a crown this morning and gave it to you.

221
00:17:53,460 --> 00:17:57,540
Yes. I've had Vice Principal Luna
put it somewhere for safekeeping.

222
00:17:57,740 --> 00:18:00,190
No idea how it ended up
in the front lawn.

223
00:18:00,320 --> 00:18:04,100
Were you interested in running
for Princess of the Fall Formal this year?

224
00:18:04,230 --> 00:18:06,150
Uh, no. Not exactly.

225
00:18:06,290 --> 00:18:08,980
The truth is...
Well, the truth is I...

226
00:18:09,110 --> 00:18:11,770
You see, the crown is actually...

227
00:18:11,900 --> 00:18:13,730
Princess of the Fall Formal?

228
00:18:13,730 --> 00:18:15,730
It's Canterlot High's big Fall dance.

229
00:18:15,860 --> 00:18:19,900
- Like the Grand Galloping Gala!
- Grand Galloping Gala?

230
00:18:20,760 --> 00:18:25,240
It was a big deal at my old school.

231
00:18:25,370 --> 00:18:26,740
And was there a princess?

232
00:18:26,870 --> 00:18:29,660
Yes, but she wasn't exactly a student.

233
00:18:29,790 --> 00:18:31,230
Here at Canterlot High,

234
00:18:31,360 --> 00:18:33,720
the students select one
of their peers to represent them.

235
00:18:33,850 --> 00:18:36,330
She receives a crown
at the Fall Formal.

236
00:18:37,330 --> 00:18:40,300
You asked me if I was interested
in running for Princess.

237
00:18:40,430 --> 00:18:42,000
Can anyone run?

238
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:44,873
Yes. You just need to let the head
of the Fall Formal planning committee

239
00:18:44,999 --> 00:18:46,460
know you'd like to be on the ballot.

240
00:18:46,590 --> 00:18:48,020
Was there anything else?

241
00:18:48,150 --> 00:18:50,850
Um, nope! That was it!

242
00:18:50,980 --> 00:18:54,020
Well, if you do need anything else,
my door is always open.

243
00:18:55,870 --> 00:18:58,610
Twilight, why didn't you just
tell her the crown was yours

244
00:18:58,740 --> 00:19:01,860
- ...and ask for it back?
-  I was going to.

245
00:19:01,990 --> 00:19:03,918
But imagine if one of them
showed up in Equestria

246
00:19:04,050 --> 00:19:05,870
saying they came from a place
filled with tall,

247
00:19:05,870 --> 00:19:08,300
fleshy, two-legged creatures
with these?

248
00:19:08,300 --> 00:19:09,880
We'd think they were crazy!

249
00:19:11,660 --> 00:19:13,390
Hmm. You make a good point.

250
00:19:13,520 --> 00:19:15,250
Looks like if I want my crown back,

251
00:19:15,380 --> 00:19:18,420
I'll have to become Princess
of the Canterlot High Fall Formal.

252
00:19:18,550 --> 00:19:20,730
So that's what I'm gonna do!

253
00:19:22,090 --> 00:19:24,690
And how exactly
do you plan on doing that?

254
00:19:24,690 --> 00:19:27,480
I have no idea!

255
00:19:41,580 --> 00:19:43,160
I know we've just met,

256
00:19:43,290 --> 00:19:46,090
but I was wondering if you might
be able to help me with something.

257
00:19:46,220 --> 00:19:47,430
Of course!

258
00:19:49,080 --> 00:19:52,240
I've decided to run for
Princess of the Fall Formal, and–

259
00:19:54,160 --> 00:19:55,230
Oh, gosh!

260
00:19:55,840 --> 00:19:59,160
Sorry. It's just,
running for Fall Formal Princess

261
00:19:59,290 --> 00:20:01,160
is a really bad idea.

262
00:20:01,290 --> 00:20:01,970
Why?

263
00:20:02,100 --> 00:20:04,960
Sunset Shimmer wants
to be Fall Formal Princess.

264
00:20:05,090 --> 00:20:08,060
And when she wants something,
she gets it!

265
00:20:08,190 --> 00:20:11,220
She'll make life awful for anyone
who stands in her way.

266
00:20:11,350 --> 00:20:15,550
Just ask the girl who ran against her
for Princess of the Spring Fling.

267
00:20:15,920 --> 00:20:17,630
I have to try!

268
00:20:18,080 --> 00:20:20,160
I don't think you understand.

269
00:20:20,290 --> 00:20:23,730
You'd have to convince everyone here
to vote for you instead of her.

270
00:20:23,860 --> 00:20:25,060
The athletes.

271
00:20:25,190 --> 00:20:26,900
The fashionistas.

272
00:20:27,030 --> 00:20:28,410
The dramas.

273
00:20:28,530 --> 00:20:30,320
The eco-kids.

274
00:20:30,450 --> 00:20:31,660
The techies.

275
00:20:31,790 --> 00:20:32,990
The rockers...

276
00:20:33,370 --> 00:20:34,950
Why is everypony–

277
00:20:36,540 --> 00:20:39,710
Everybody separated this way?

278
00:20:39,840 --> 00:20:41,830
Maybe it was different
at your old school,

279
00:20:41,960 --> 00:20:45,460
but at C.H.S.,
everybody sticks to their own kind.

280
00:20:45,590 --> 00:20:47,700
One thing that they do have in common

281
00:20:47,830 --> 00:20:52,500
is that they know Sunset Shimmer
is gonna rule the school until we graduate.

282
00:20:52,630 --> 00:20:53,990
Not if I can help it!

283
00:21:00,360 --> 00:21:01,820
So...

284
00:21:02,230 --> 00:21:04,820
Where would I find the head
of the party planning committee?

285
00:21:07,850 --> 00:21:10,660
Fluttershy said
she'd probably be in here.

286
00:21:12,290 --> 00:21:14,850
Incoming!

287
00:21:23,140 --> 00:21:25,910
Hi, my name's Twilight Sparkle and...

288
00:21:26,040 --> 00:21:27,180
Pinkie Pie?

289
00:21:30,690 --> 00:21:31,910
Are you psychic?!

290
00:21:32,040 --> 00:21:34,320
Uh, no. I don't think so.

291
00:21:34,450 --> 00:21:36,820
Unless of course that's something
you can do here.

292
00:21:36,950 --> 00:21:38,330
Not usually.

293
00:21:40,100 --> 00:21:41,466
Fluttershy said this is where

294
00:21:41,597 --> 00:21:43,826
I'd find the head of the
Fall Formal planning committee.

295
00:21:43,850 --> 00:21:45,490
Fluttershy, huh?

296
00:21:46,330 --> 00:21:48,464
Don't let the whole "shy" thing fool you.

297
00:21:48,594 --> 00:21:50,071
She can be a real meanie.

298
00:21:50,280 --> 00:21:52,040
You two aren't friends?

299
00:21:52,180 --> 00:21:54,360
Waited a bit to get your name
on the ballot, huh?

300
00:21:54,490 --> 00:21:56,200
Dance is day after tomorrow.

301
00:21:56,330 --> 00:21:57,450
I'm brand new here.

302
00:21:59,680 --> 00:22:01,550
I thought you didn't look familiar.

303
00:22:01,680 --> 00:22:04,930
Though, now that
I'm really lookin' at you...

304
00:22:05,350 --> 00:22:08,150
Do you have a twin sister who lives
in the city, has a pet dog named Spike

305
00:22:08,320 --> 00:22:10,840
that looks just like that one?

306
00:22:11,300 --> 00:22:14,180
- Uh, maybe?
- Thought so.

307
00:22:14,310 --> 00:22:17,760
Anywho, just need to fill this out
and you are officially up for the coveted

308
00:22:17,890 --> 00:22:20,770
Princess of the Fall Formal crown.

309
00:22:36,570 --> 00:22:39,280
You have really bad handwriting.

310
00:22:39,410 --> 00:22:41,630
It's like you've never
held a pen before.

311
00:22:43,100 --> 00:22:44,280
Is it?

312
00:22:44,410 --> 00:22:47,500
Somebody order a dozen cases
of fizzy apple cider?

313
00:22:47,500 --> 00:22:50,770
Oh! Oh! Me, me-me-me, me,
yeah, ha ha, me!

314
00:22:52,970 --> 00:22:55,720
- Can you bring in the rest?
- Eeyup.

315
00:22:59,130 --> 00:23:02,190
- Hey, I know you.
- You do?

316
00:23:02,320 --> 00:23:06,250
Sure. You're the new girl who gave
Sunset Shimmer the what for today.

317
00:23:07,490 --> 00:23:10,530
Twilight Sparkle here is going
to run against Sunset Shimmer

318
00:23:10,660 --> 00:23:12,550
for Princess of the Fall Formal.

319
00:23:14,830 --> 00:23:16,730
I'd think twice about that.

320
00:23:16,860 --> 00:23:19,600
Oh, sure, she'll probably
approach you all friendly like...

321
00:23:22,490 --> 00:23:26,140
<i>"I sure am lookin' forward
to some friendly competition."</i>

322
00:23:26,270 --> 00:23:28,130
<i>"That's so good to hear!"</i>

323
00:23:28,280 --> 00:23:30,790
But then,
here comes the backstabbin'.

324
00:23:31,800 --> 00:23:34,680
About the only girl in this school
you can trust less than Sunset Shimmer

325
00:23:34,810 --> 00:23:36,380
is Rainbow Dash.

326
00:23:36,520 --> 00:23:37,800
Rainbow Dash?

327
00:23:37,930 --> 00:23:42,070
She's the captain of, like,
every team at Canterlot High.

328
00:23:42,200 --> 00:23:45,300
She's also the captain of sayin'
she's gonna do somethin' for ya,

329
00:23:45,430 --> 00:23:48,120
and then turnin' around
and not even botherin' to show up.

330
00:23:48,250 --> 00:23:49,769
Thanks for the advice, Applejack.

331
00:23:49,899 --> 00:23:52,051
But this is something
I really need to do.

332
00:23:52,250 --> 00:23:53,730
Suit yourself.

333
00:23:53,860 --> 00:23:56,990
Hey, how'd you know
my name was Applejack?

334
00:23:59,330 --> 00:24:02,740
- Didn't you say?
- Nope.

335
00:24:02,870 --> 00:24:05,080
Well, it sure was sure nice
meeting you both.

336
00:24:05,220 --> 00:24:06,870
I'm sure I'll be seeing you around.

337
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:12,940
That one's trying to hide a secret,
but I am totally on to her.

338
00:24:13,300 --> 00:24:15,830
She's psychic!

339
00:24:16,650 --> 00:24:18,320
If you say so.

340
00:24:19,490 --> 00:24:21,900
This looks terrible!

341
00:24:23,300 --> 00:24:26,040
There should be more streamers
near the stage and fewer balloons.

342
00:24:27,640 --> 00:24:29,820
Yeah, streamers!

343
00:24:30,110 --> 00:24:32,050
And fewer balloons!

344
00:24:33,900 --> 00:24:35,700
Fizzy apple cider?

345
00:24:36,440 --> 00:24:39,070
This is my coronation,
not a hoedown!

346
00:24:39,530 --> 00:24:41,140
Well, now,

347
00:24:41,270 --> 00:24:45,720
it ain't necessarily gonna be
your coronation this time around.

348
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:47,760
Oh, is that so?

349
00:24:47,890 --> 00:24:50,620
You country folk
really aren't that bright.

350
00:24:50,750 --> 00:24:54,600
Must be why the other students
say such awful things about you.

351
00:24:56,320 --> 00:24:59,330
Obviously it's gonna be MY coronation.

352
00:24:59,460 --> 00:25:01,550
I'm running unopposed.

353
00:25:01,680 --> 00:25:04,770
Not this time.
The new girl just signed up!

354
00:25:04,870 --> 00:25:06,020
What?!

355
00:25:06,930 --> 00:25:10,100
I know.
Her handwriting is really bad.

356
00:25:10,530 --> 00:25:13,360
Where is this Twilight Sparkle?

357
00:25:15,870 --> 00:25:19,610
I'm looking forward
to meeting the competition!

358
00:25:32,210 --> 00:25:35,720
Can't believe
I didn't recognize you earlier.

359
00:25:36,380 --> 00:25:40,720
Should've known Princess Celestia would
send her prized pupil here after my crown.

360
00:25:40,850 --> 00:25:42,550
And her little dog, too.

361
00:25:42,680 --> 00:25:44,560
It's MY crown!

362
00:25:44,690 --> 00:25:47,890
Whatever.
This is just a minor setback for me.

363
00:25:48,020 --> 00:25:50,008
You don't know the first thing
about this place,

364
00:25:50,138 --> 00:25:52,140
and I already rule it.

365
00:25:52,270 --> 00:25:54,830
If that's so,
why do you even need my crown?

366
00:25:54,960 --> 00:25:58,410
You went to an awful lot of trouble
to switch it with the one that belongs here.

367
00:25:58,540 --> 00:25:59,522
Pop quiz:

368
00:25:59,652 --> 00:26:03,750
what happens when you bring an
Element of Harmony into an alternate world?

369
00:26:04,430 --> 00:26:07,240
You don't know? Seriously?

370
00:26:08,410 --> 00:26:12,740
And you're supposed to be
Princess Celestia's star student?

371
00:26:13,620 --> 00:26:17,690
Then again, what were the chances
she'd find somepony as bright as me

372
00:26:17,820 --> 00:26:20,710
to take under her wing
after I decided to leave Equestria?

373
00:26:20,840 --> 00:26:24,530
Bit embarrassing that you
were the best she could do.

374
00:26:25,519 --> 00:26:28,830
Oh, and I'd keep an eye on your mutt.

375
00:26:28,960 --> 00:26:31,730
Hate for him to be...
taken away from you.

376
00:26:31,860 --> 00:26:33,800
Is that a threat?

377
00:26:33,930 --> 00:26:35,980
Oh, of course not.

378
00:26:36,930 --> 00:26:40,190
But I'd cut down on the chatter
if I were you.

379
00:26:40,320 --> 00:26:44,150
Don't want everyone to know you two
don't belong here, now would you?

380
00:26:44,320 --> 00:26:47,580
You want to be a princess here?
Please.

381
00:26:48,700 --> 00:26:51,630
You don't know the first thing
about fitting in.

382
00:27:04,300 --> 00:27:06,340
I want you to follow her.

383
00:27:06,470 --> 00:27:09,000
Bring me something I can use
just like you did with that last girl

384
00:27:09,130 --> 00:27:11,260
who thought she could challenge me.

385
00:27:11,490 --> 00:27:13,660
You got it, Sunset Shimmer.

386
00:27:13,900 --> 00:27:16,810
When the crown
and its power are mine,

387
00:27:16,940 --> 00:27:20,820
Twilight Sparkle will be sorry
she ever set hoof into this world!

388
00:27:20,950 --> 00:27:24,520
Not that she would've been much safer
if she'd stayed in Equestria.

389
00:27:25,230 --> 00:27:28,220
Yeah, in Equestria.

390
00:27:28,350 --> 00:27:29,680
What are you still doing here?!

391
00:27:29,820 --> 00:27:30,950
Go!

392
00:27:55,060 --> 00:27:56,730
Excuse me.

393
00:27:57,470 --> 00:28:01,140
The Great and Powerful Trixie!

394
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:04,000
...Needs some peanut butter crackers.

395
00:28:06,860 --> 00:28:08,690
Voilà!

396
00:28:10,770 --> 00:28:12,710
Sunset Shimmer is right.

397
00:28:12,910 --> 00:28:15,020
I don't know the first thing
about this place.

398
00:28:15,150 --> 00:28:17,300
If I'm gonna really fit in
and win votes,

399
00:28:17,430 --> 00:28:19,040
we need to do some research.

400
00:28:19,170 --> 00:28:21,160
Research?

401
00:28:21,290 --> 00:28:24,680
This place has a school.
I have to believe it's got a...

402
00:28:24,970 --> 00:28:26,740
library!

403
00:28:29,230 --> 00:28:30,600
Got your phone?

404
00:28:31,610 --> 00:28:33,030
Got yours?

405
00:28:44,850 --> 00:28:48,430
So I just push the letters here,

406
00:28:48,560 --> 00:28:52,220
and then the words and moving
pictures will come up here?

407
00:28:55,900 --> 00:28:57,790
That's right.

408
00:28:59,590 --> 00:29:01,930
Maybe this place does have magic.

409
00:29:10,270 --> 00:29:12,610
<i>When you're a younger–</i>

410
00:29:13,330 --> 00:29:15,680
Girls! What are you doing?

411
00:29:15,810 --> 00:29:18,940
We're just seeing how many hits
our new music video has gotten.

412
00:29:19,660 --> 00:29:22,570
<i>So the three of us
will fight the fight...</i>

413
00:29:22,700 --> 00:29:24,400
No, just...

414
00:29:24,400 --> 00:29:25,930
No!

415
00:29:26,060 --> 00:29:29,570
The school computers are
for research purposes only.

416
00:29:29,700 --> 00:29:31,400
It's just as well, y'all.

417
00:29:31,530 --> 00:29:34,220
Some of the comments about our song
were really awful.

418
00:29:34,350 --> 00:29:36,240
"Epic Fail."

419
00:29:36,370 --> 00:29:38,070
"Funniest thing I've ever seen"?!

420
00:29:38,200 --> 00:29:41,710
Funniest thing they've ever seen,
huh?

421
00:29:41,860 --> 00:29:45,330
Uh, I don't know that
that's what you should take from...

422
00:30:34,150 --> 00:30:37,560
<i>The library will be closing
in five minutes. </i>

423
00:30:40,100 --> 00:30:43,020
I hadn't even thought about
where we're going to sleep tonight!

424
00:30:44,460 --> 00:30:46,110
Way ahead of you.

425
00:30:50,120 --> 00:30:52,670
It's a little... dusty.

426
00:30:52,800 --> 00:30:56,030
But it doesn't seem like
anybody comes up here

427
00:30:56,680 --> 00:30:58,370
It's perfect, Spike.

428
00:31:03,200 --> 00:31:06,460
- So, how did your research go?
- I found this book.

429
00:31:06,590 --> 00:31:08,250
It's called a yearbook.

430
00:31:08,380 --> 00:31:10,815
It seems to be something
they use to keep a record of things

431
00:31:10,945 --> 00:31:12,510
that have happened at the school.

432
00:31:12,690 --> 00:31:15,010
Look. That's Pinkie Pie,

433
00:31:15,140 --> 00:31:18,680
Rainbow Dash, Applejack,
Fluttershy...

434
00:31:18,810 --> 00:31:20,680
and I'm gonna bet
the girl on the far right is Rarity.

435
00:31:20,810 --> 00:31:22,480
There's a Rarity here!?

436
00:31:23,060 --> 00:31:25,930
Uh, I mean, uh... interesting photo.

437
00:31:26,060 --> 00:31:29,080
It's interesting because
they look like they're friends.

438
00:31:29,210 --> 00:31:31,150
They do look like our friends.

439
00:31:31,280 --> 00:31:33,120
But I thought
we figured that out already.

440
00:31:33,250 --> 00:31:34,700
No, I mean...

441
00:31:34,830 --> 00:31:37,150
they look like they're friends
with each other.

442
00:31:37,340 --> 00:31:40,080
But it doesn't seem like
they're friends now.

443
00:31:40,210 --> 00:31:41,660
Not so much.

444
00:31:41,960 --> 00:31:43,698
I just can't help but get the feeling

445
00:31:43,838 --> 00:31:45,910
that Sunset Shimmer
had something to do with it.

446
00:31:46,040 --> 00:31:48,080
I wouldn't put it past her.

447
00:31:48,880 --> 00:31:50,256
But she wanted your crown

448
00:31:50,386 --> 00:31:52,840
'cause she's planning on doing
something even worse!

449
00:31:52,970 --> 00:31:54,516
If you're gonna stop her,

450
00:31:54,647 --> 00:31:56,500
you have to focus
on making friends here.

451
00:31:56,630 --> 00:31:58,980
Can't worry about why
these girls aren't friends anymore.

452
00:31:59,110 --> 00:32:04,200
Even if they do remind you
of your Ponyville friends.

453
00:32:04,400 --> 00:32:06,200
You're right, Spike.

454
00:32:07,190 --> 00:32:09,190
Eye on the prize.

455
00:32:12,830 --> 00:32:15,240
<i>Good morning, students,
and happy Thursday.</i>

456
00:32:15,370 --> 00:32:19,150
<i>Just a reminder to pick up your ballots
for the Princess of the Fall Formal today.</i>

457
00:32:19,280 --> 00:32:21,230
<i>They are due at the time
the dance starts tomorrow night, </i>

458
00:32:21,360 --> 00:32:23,700
<i>so don't forget to turn them in
and make your voice heard. </i>

459
00:32:23,960 --> 00:32:26,450
Fluttershy said I'd need to win over
all those different groups

460
00:32:26,580 --> 00:32:28,710
if I want to become
Princess of the Fall Formal.

461
00:32:28,840 --> 00:32:30,920
So I've compiled
a list of talking points.

462
00:32:32,000 --> 00:32:35,130
You made a list?
That's so unlike you!

463
00:32:38,781 --> 00:32:41,370
Uh... Please. Continue.

464
00:32:41,500 --> 00:32:43,310
I'll start introducing myself.

465
00:32:43,440 --> 00:32:46,640
Sprinkle in some things I've learned
about their world into the conversation.

466
00:32:46,770 --> 00:32:48,550
Show them how I fit in here!

467
00:32:51,960 --> 00:32:53,230
Okay, Spike.

468
00:32:53,360 --> 00:32:56,070
Time to make a good first impression
on my fellow students.

469
00:32:59,420 --> 00:33:02,080
The whole world
sort of depends on it.

470
00:33:02,210 --> 00:33:03,700
Hey, look.

471
00:33:10,990 --> 00:33:13,300
Why is everybody looking at me funny?

472
00:33:14,750 --> 00:33:17,460
What're you...? Why did you...?

473
00:33:17,590 --> 00:33:18,800
Rarity?

474
00:33:27,630 --> 00:33:31,980
Oh, yes. This is good!
No one will recognize you!

475
00:33:32,110 --> 00:33:33,530
Why wouldn't I want to be–

476
00:33:33,530 --> 00:33:35,230
And we'll need a disguise for your dog.

477
00:33:35,360 --> 00:33:39,740
Which is too bad.
He really is so adorable!

478
00:33:39,870 --> 00:33:41,263
You know, with a little work,

479
00:33:41,393 --> 00:33:44,150
I think I could make him
look like a rabbit instead.

480
00:33:44,280 --> 00:33:45,780
A rabbit?

481
00:33:46,080 --> 00:33:47,660
There you are, Twilight.

482
00:33:47,790 --> 00:33:49,920
So much for the disguise.

483
00:33:50,050 --> 00:33:51,580
I've been lookin' all over for ya!

484
00:33:51,710 --> 00:33:53,930
- Me too.
- Me three!

485
00:33:55,180 --> 00:33:56,670
I like your new look!

486
00:33:56,800 --> 00:33:58,950
I do have an eye
for these sorts of things.

487
00:33:59,080 --> 00:34:00,480
Not that you seem to care.

488
00:34:00,480 --> 00:34:01,590
What?!

489
00:34:01,720 --> 00:34:03,040
Why do you think she doesn't care?

490
00:34:04,890 --> 00:34:06,320
No, never mind.

491
00:34:06,450 --> 00:34:07,841
Why were you all looking for me?

492
00:34:07,971 --> 00:34:09,300
What's going on?

493
00:34:09,840 --> 00:34:11,930
She hasn't seen it yet.

494
00:34:12,060 --> 00:34:13,280
Seen what?

495
00:34:15,410 --> 00:34:17,530
Oh, it's really not that bad.

496
00:34:18,350 --> 00:34:22,600
<i>Twilight Sparkle wants to be
your Fall Formal Princess.</i>

497
00:34:24,610 --> 00:34:29,430
<i>What does it say about our school
if we give someone like this...</i>

498
00:34:31,330 --> 00:34:33,840
<i>such an important honor? </i>

499
00:34:38,210 --> 00:34:41,580
I take that back.
It's pretty bad!

500
00:34:41,710 --> 00:34:44,630
But this all happened yesterday!
At the library!

501
